A domestic staff identified as Joseph Ogbu 20, has been arrested by police over the gruesome murder of his employer and her mother. Disclosing this Thursday the Lagos state police public relations officer, a deputy superintendent of police said on 20th June, 2019 at about 3: 00am, Surulere Police Station received a distress call from No 4 Ogulana drive, Surulere that one Joseph Ogbu from Oju Local Government Area, Benue State, who was employed as a domestic staff on 18th June, 2019, murdered his female employer Oreoluwa John aged 38 and her mother, Adejoke John aged 89 at their above mentioned resident. The suspect he said, confessed to the crime and averred in his statement that his employer asked him to clean the house at about 9; 00pm of 19th June, 2019 but an argument ensued between them, which prompted him to stab her with a knife. He added that the shock of her dead made her aged mother to slum and die. Considering the fact that they are dead, he moved some valuable properties such as electronics, handsets and household items into the employerâ€™s Toyota Camry Salon Car and attempted to escape to where he cannot be found, before he was apprehended by Policemen on patrol at Ogunlana pindown point. Dsp Bala revealed that the vehicle and items stolen were recovered while the crime scene was sealed off and corpses of the two victims were taken to Mainland hospital Yaba for autopsy. Bala also disclosed that the Commissioner of Police Lagos State, CP Zubairu Muazu On has ordered the State Criminal Investigation Department, Yaba to take over the investigation and charge the suspect to Court.